cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with trajectory planning for robots. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses optimization formulations for trajectory planning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a damage quantification function and studies its influence on the trajectory. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper may involve learning-based approaches for collision-tolerant trajectory planning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as computer vision techniques may be used for collision detection and avoidance.
